Online Quiz Management System
A full-featured Spring Boot-based backend system that allows users to take quizzes composed of multiple-choice questions. It also includes an admin panel for managing quizzes and questions.

📌 Overview
The Online Quiz Management System enables users to participate in quizzes containing multiple-choice questions. The platform provides full administrative control for managing quizzes and questions while also allowing participants to attempt quizzes and receive instant evaluations.

🔑 Features
✅ Create quizzes and associate multiple questions

✅ Add, update, or delete quiz questions

✅ Attempt quizzes and receive scores based on correct answers

✅ Retrieve quiz details with all associated questions

✅ Admin panel for secure quiz and question management

🗂️ Entities and Relationships
Quiz
Fields: id, title, description, List<Question> questions

Question
Fields: id, questionText, options[], correctAnswer

Relationship:
One Quiz has many Questions (One-to-Many relationship)

🛠️ Tech Stack
Layer	Technology
Backend	Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA
ORM	Hibernate
Database	MySQL
API Testing	Postman
Build Tool	Maven
Language	Java

📥 API Functionalities
Create Quiz with a list of questions

Add/Edit/Delete individual questions

Retrieve Quiz Details (including all questions)

Evaluate Quiz based on submitted answers

Admin APIs for managing quizzes and questions

📚 How to Run
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/OnlineQuizSystem.git
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy
Edit
cd OnlineQuizSystem
Configure your MySQL database in application.properties:

properties
Copy
Edit
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/quizdb
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=yourpassword
Build and run the application:

bash
Copy
Edit
mvn spring-boot:run
Test the API endpoints using Postman or any REST client.

